NORMALISED EXTRACT
Enabling ESM in Node.js:
- Use .mjs file extension OR set package.json "type": "module" OR run node with --input-type=module for single-run scripts.
- If code contains ES module syntax and lacks explicit markers, Node.js may detect and run as ESM.

Import specifiers and types:
- Three specifier types: relative (./file.js) - require file extension; bare (package-name) - resolved via package exports; absolute (file:///abs/path).
- Relative specifiers must include file extensions and fully specified directory indexes.
- Bare specifiers resolved by Node module resolution and respect package.json "exports" field.

import.meta properties and methods:
- import.meta.url -> absolute file: URL of current module.
- import.meta.filename -> absolute path with symlinks resolved (file modules only).
- import.meta.dirname -> directory name of current module.
- import.meta.main -> boolean true when module is entry point.
- import.meta.resolve(specifier) -> returns absolute URL string for resolution; may perform synchronous FS ops.

CommonJS interoperability:
- Importing CommonJS from ESM: module.exports provided as default export; best-effort static analysis exposes named exports.
- Use module.createRequire() inside ESM to obtain require() behavior when necessary.
- Dynamic import() works in both module systems for asynchronous loading.

File extension and resolution rules:
- Mandatory file extensions for import statements in ESM for relative/absolute specifiers.
- data:, node:, and file: URL schemes supported; data: supports text/javascript, application/json, application/wasm for imports.
- file URLs with different queries/fragments are treated as distinct modules (can cause multiple loads).

SUPPLEMENTARY DETAILS
- import.meta.resolve(specifier) signature: import.meta.resolve(specifier[, parentURL]) -> string (absolute URL). parentURL optional in experimental mode.
- Use url.pathToFileURL for building file: URLs for import operations.
- Node.js supports import attributes with { type: 'json' } for JSON modules.

REFERENCE DETAILS
- Node ESM enablement options: file extensions (.mjs), package.json "type":"module", CLI flags --input-type=module
- import.meta API: properties: url (string), filename (string), dirname (string), main (boolean); method: resolve(specifier) -> string
- CommonJS import mapping: default export maps to module.exports; named exports inferred via static analysis but not live-bound.

